The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 The IFA has sent a showcause letter to East Bengal club asking Alvito D Cunha to reply at the earliest for his misdemeanour in the CFL Premier Division match against Eastern Railway. East Bengal captain, soon after scoring the matchwinner, made obscene gestures at the rival goalie and even hit him. 

 Bimal Mahato and Rina Das were given a warm send off on Tuesday by the Athletics Coaches Association of Bengal prior to their departure for Bangkok to participate in the Standard Chartered Bangkok Marathon on Sunday. 

 They will leave the city on Friday. 

 The South Calcutta District Table Tennis Meet will be held at the Lake Athletic Club in Santoshpur from December 8-11. The last date of entry at the BTTA office has been fixed on December 3.

 TENNIS: Inter-school meet at the SAI courts from 10 am.




